# n8n Workflow Rules

When working with files in `n8n/`, follow these conventions:

## Skill

For non-trivial n8n work (creating workflows, debugging pipelines, deploying),
read the `n8n-workflow` skill at `.cursor/skills/n8n-workflow/SKILL.md`.

## Quick Reference

### Environment

Credentials live in `.env.local` (gitignored). Source it before making API calls:

```bash
source .env.local
```

### Commands

- `npm run n8n:list` -- list all workflows on Cloud
- `npm run n8n:pull` -- pull all workflows from Cloud to `n8n/workflows/`
- `npm run n8n:push` -- push all local workflow JSON files to Cloud
- `npm run n8n:credentials` -- list credential IDs available on Cloud
- `./.cursor/skills/n8n-workflow/sync.sh <command>` -- full sync script (see `--help`)

### After Deploying

Always commit workflow JSON to git after pushing to n8n Cloud, so the repo
stays in sync as the source of truth.

